# CLI Usage: Command Line Interface

The [main.py](mdc:absrefined/main.py) file provides a command-line interface for the application. 

Key arguments:
- `item_specifier`: Positional argument for the Item ID or full Item URL.
- `--config`: Path to the `config.toml` file (default: `config.toml`).
- `--model`: Override LLM model from config.
- `--window`: Override search window size (seconds) from config.
- `--download-path`: Override temporary download path from config.
- `--dry-run`: Don't actually update the server.
- `--yes` / `-y`: Auto-confirm server updates.
- `--just-download`: Only download the audio file and exit.
- `--verbose` / `-v`: Enable INFO logging (overrides config).
- `--debug`: Enable DEBUG logging (overrides config).

Configuration (API keys, server URL, default model/window/paths, etc.) is primarily managed via the `config.toml` file. See [config-handling.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/config-handling.mdc)
